column1: You're now almost finished the task! In the last part, you will do another memory test. You will be shown an image, like below, on each trial. Your job is to indicate whether you have seen this image before at ANY point in the task. If you have seen the image before, press 'f' to indicate that it is old. If you haven't seen this image before, press 'j' to indicate the image is new.
Since you have seen the book before, you should select 'f' to indicate the book is old.
This test is timed. You have a limit of 2 seconds to respond. So try to respond as quickly as possible.
First we will do a practice. When you’re ready to start the practice, press the space bar.
There are now only a few more questions left! Please press space to continue.
There are now only a few more questions left! Please press space to continue.

During the task you first learned a list a image pairs - let's call these pairs Image A and B. For example, you learned that the book (image A) was paired with the woman, Jessica alba (Image B).Later in the task, you learned that one of the images in the pair (Image A - the book) was paired with a different image (Image C - the animal, alpaca).
column2: Question: When you learned the later pairs (images A and C), like the book and alpaca, did you actively think about the earlier pair that you had learned, like the book and the girl, Jessica Alba (images A and B)?  Press 'y' for yes and 'n' for no.

column1: If you answered no to the earlier question, press space to proceed. If you answered yes, that you actively thought about the earlier pairs (Images A and B) when you learned the later pairs (Images A and C), did you mostly think about the connection between image pairs when you saw  the later pairs (Image A and C), or during the arrow task, or both? Press 'J' if you mostly thought about the connection between image pairs when you learned the later image pairs. Press 'K' if you mostly thought about the connection between image pairs during the arrow task. Press 'L' if you thought about the connections between the image pairs when you learned the later pair AND during the arrow task.
During the arrow task, please rate your boredom on a scale of 1 to 7. With 1 being not bored at all, 4 being neutral, and 7 being completely bored.
How interested were you in the task? With 1 being not interested at all, 4 being neutral, and 7 being very interested.

How often did your mind drift away from the task during the arrow task to other concerns or daydreams. Please rate your mind wandering on a scale of 1 to 7. With 1 being not at mind wandering and totally focused on the task the whole time, 4 being sometimes daydreaming and thinking about other concerns, and 7 being daydreaming and/or thinking about other concerns the majority of the time.
How motivated were you to do well on the memory task? With 1 being not motivated at all, 4 being a kind of motivated and 7 being very motivated to do well on the memory task.
How much stress did you experience this week? With 1 being no stress, 4 being some stress, and 7 being a lot of stress?
